The Energy Transfer  ETGO Chalmette Cryo (herinafter referred to as Stationary Source) will be a Program 3 process under the ARP Program based on the following criteria:
	The Stationary Source stores greater than the threshold quantities of regulated substances,
	A worst case release of a regulated substance would affect public receptors, and
	It is a manned Stationary Source that is subject to OSHA PSM regulation.
This report document the steps taken to determine the program applicability and develop the Risk Management Plan (RMP) for the Stationary Source. These steps include:
	Verification of program applicability;
	Verification of chemical quantities in each process and largest vessel quantity;
	Completion of the off site consequence analysis and impacts; and
	Update of the five year accident history
This report documents the steps taken to confirm the program applicability of the Risk Management Plan (RMP) for the Stationary Source. These steps include:
·	Verification of program applicability;
·	Review and update of chemical quantities in each process and largest vessel quantity;
·	Review and update of the off-site consequence analysis and impacts;
·	Update and re-validate PHA;
·	Verification that refresher training of operating procedures has been completed;
·	Verification of adequacy and implementation of compliance audits for procedures and practices;
·	Verification that maintenance/mechanical integrity has been inspected and tested;
·	Verification that annual certifications of operating procedures are current and accurate;
·	Verification that any changes within a covered process is properly updated in the process safety information and Stationary Source procedures and practices;
·	Update of the five-year accident history;
·	Verification that process information is current and that each covered process still meets the eligibility for its program level;
